AMEBIASIS - CHILE (TALTAL)
==========================
Date: Mon, 10 Mar 97 16:13 SAT
From: Julio Salas Vergara <jsalas@pasteur.minsal.cl> (by way of SSMS
<ssms-epi@reuna.cl>)

At the express instruction of the Undersecretary of Health, Sr Fernando
Munoz P., I inform you of an outbreak of amebiasis in the locality of
Taltal, due primarily to deficient environmental conditions. It is strongly
recommended to take the proper measures to control enteric diseases, in
order to safeguard the health of the population.
[trans. by Mod.JW - original below]
--
Julio Salas Vergara
Jsalas@pasteur.minsal.cl
[Taltal is a Pacific port in north Chile, 125 miles S. of Antofagasta.
Measures to control enteric diseases normally consist of boiling drinking
water and chlorinating public water supplies - Mod.JW]
--------------------------------------------
[Spanish original]
Subject: Atencion Brote Epidemico de Amebiasis
Por medio de la presente y por expresa instruccion del Sr. Subsecretario de
Salud, Sr. Fernando Munoz P. informo a usted de la ocurrencia de un brote
epidemico de Amebiasis en la localidad de Taltal, debido prioritariamente a
condiciones ambientales deficientes, por lo cual se recomienda enfaticamente
adoptar las medidas pertinentes propias de control de enfermedades entericas
con el fin de salvaguardar la salud de la poblacion.
--
Julio Salas Vergara.
Jsalas@pasteur.minsal.cl
............................................................jw

--
